   "source": [
    "## Observations\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Only **P14 (Hungarian)** clears recall > 0.01.  It wins by not attempting an affine fit — no commitment = no lock-in to a wrong global minimum.\n",
    "2. Every **affine-committing** candidate (P1, P3, P4, P5, M3, C1) emits predictions but they are self-consistent at the *wrong* global pose (origin error 1.3–1.7 mm).\n",
    "3. **M1's NCC peak is 0.046** — too weak to act as a scale-aware warm-start.  Dominant failure mode.\n",
    "4. **I2/I3 have a load-side bug** (fixed post-sweep; not re-run here).\n",
    "5. **GNN (G1)** matches G2's behaviour — same warm-start dependency.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Headline: coarse-scale is the unsolved prerequisite\n",
    "\n",
    "The Grand Plan's M-series was intended to fill that gap; the first pass of M1 is too weak.  Strengthening M1 (wider grid, soft-mask NCC) is the priority next step, followed by re-benchmarking M3/C1 with the stronger warm-start."
   ]
